      CPU+mem-bound (bandwidth-wise), threads add nothing IMO.<br>
    </p>
    <p>Indeed a separate postmaster is very much needed in order to
      control the processes / guard overall integrity.</p>
    <p><br>
    </p>
    <p>Hence, my humble suggestion is to consider a hybrid architecture
