I don&#39;t quite buy that. A multi-threaded model isn&#39;t inherently mor=
e <br>
complex than a multi-process model. Just different. Sure, the transition <b=
r>
period will be more complex, when we need to support both models. But in <b=
r>
the long run, if we can remove the multi-process mode, we can make a lot <b=
r>
of things *simpler*.<br></blockquote><div><br></div><div>If I may weigh in =
here:=C2=A0</div><div>Making a previously unthreaded process able to handle=
 multiple threads, is a tedious process.</div><blockquote class=3D"gmail_qu=
ote" style=3D"margin:0px 0px 0px 0.8ex;border-left:1px solid rgb(204,204,20=
4);padding-left:1ex">
<br>
